Thousands of Britons were among those caught up in travel chaos today as Air France cancelled half of its flights because of strike action.

Pilots working for the troubled airline were taking action against its plan to pour more money into its low-cost subsidiary Transavia.

The strike, which is expected to cost around £15m a day, saw lengthy queues building up at major airports as thousands were stranded.

