‘It’s an absolutely chaotic situation – I’m desperate to get to Nice from Paris but nothing seems to be moving,’ said businessman David Newman, who is originally from Birmingham.

‘Lots of services have been cancelled completely, but information is very hard to come by. It’s a ridiculous situation. 

‘Air travel in France is always being hit by strikes – the country needs to sort this matter out.’

Britons are the biggest visitor group in the world to Paris, while thousands of others use France as a hub to get to other parts of the world. 

Air France sent 65,000 text messages to passengers warning them about cancellations and delays, but thousands just turned up anyway.

A company spokesman urged those ‘who have booked a flight between September 15 and 22 to delay their trip, change their ticket free of charge or claim a refund.’

